KGW Manifesto

The Abundance of Slowness

Matt Steel
Workaholics aren't heroes. They don't save the day, they just use it up. The real hero is already home because she figured out a faster way to get things done. - Jason Fried & David Heinemeier Hansson. In March of 2011, I was in the depths of burnout...
What we’re ultimately striving for here is a joyful harmony between work, rest and play…. This week, I invite you to try nine things:
  1. Slow down.
  2. Stop trying to be a hero.
  3. Go home.
  4. Minimize meetings.
  5. Go dark.
  6. Leave your desk for lunch.
  7. Give up on multitasking.
  8. Say no.
  9. Hunt your fear.
